column5: Sweet ride Terry, congrats! I hope it gives you years of satisfaction... with that said, you've had it almost a week, what have you broke on it? LOL HH
so far so good measure twice drill hole once
If you need more,just howlla.
awesome ride .. like my bros new Rig... Love your rod holder setup!
Excellent boat. I thought It very interesting you choose to rig it yourself. Its the smartest thing a guy could do. Congrats
Sweet, I have the same rig but 2011, you'll love it.
nice boat but where and when did the fence get there?

Fishing boat that you can't slime.  Lol.  It ain't that hard to clean off. Hey stop catching fish your getting my boat slimed.  Last time I was in a boat like that buddy broke me off.   Sucks cause it was a big pike with a kick butt lure.  What a numbnut.  Congrats she's a beauty.
yes there  is a cover for it
I can hear the good Ol folding boat crying right now  great looking ride Terry Im looking forward to the reports coming from the trips out on her

took it out for a spin no fishing just trying to get though the break in period ... dang 40 bucks in fuel in an hour and 15 minutes going 4000 to 5400 rpm hope it gets better once it spots using twice the oil
Already complaining. LOL
yeah but the wife didn't want to share the gas expense....good partner but not much of a fishing partner
Sweet ride Terry!!!
Captain at the helm.
Awesome rig! I'm sure many a fish will be hoisted over the gunnels in that one!

Very nice rig Terry I am glad it also all came in. I am sure when the 9.9 gets in you will be made whole. I was once asked by a buddy as we drove to the boat what my truck got for mileage and I replied "16 combined" he said "ouch" I said "meeh that not so bad the boat we are taking out get 1 1/2 MPG."   Art
lol  yeah, we know this,  the price you pay for toys....is just the start of what it will cost
Got those riggers on yet?
no I am missing a bracket, so I have not figured out how to put them on yet  I have the nylon being glued on as we speak
looks real good Terry.  But why are you glueing your nylons on?
Takes longer for the "Johns" to get them off and he gets paid by the hour....
lol  lol  hang on I have one more in me   lol  funny stuff  it is a piece of nylon or some material like that glued on the transom, so no drilling into boat under the water line
BOAT = Bust Out Another Thousand  Without gas in the boat she just looks good in the driveway.
BAAAHAHAHAHA  Good ONE!!!
My compliments sir!
you ever wonder how he knows this stuff  lol
Sweet ride Terry, congrats!
sweet rig terry congrats
thanks guys, with all the heat, then rain Im finding it hard to get everything on it so I can get out fishing with it

it has been a real run around  dates keep changing  but got the word, it's on it's way and would be here thurs. or early friday  showed up thursday afternoon   got phone call  do you still want your boat on Saturday well yeah  OK, we have ha problem  yeah, spit it out what's wrong  well as soon as we saw the boat up on the truck we knew there was no 9.9 on it the documents say it's on back order, I am really pissed  You're pissed, I will show you pissed so what the.....many words I can't type here  many more  more    more  i would think a few more  heck are we doing about it  well it really isn't lunds fault, it's merc that did not deliver Brunswick Corp.  well yeah owned by same company  2 weeks and the good news is the boat is all pre-rigged for the motor  ok I will pick it up saturday, but I am holding back the price of the motor and what is lund going to give me those leather coats would be nice  sorry they don't have them any more  some pro brackets...  ok  so I picked it up got it home and now the fun begins  I am rigging everything myself
Awesome ride Terry.  I have the same sized Lund but an older ProV.  Great boat that will do everything you'll ever want it to.  RJ
WOOOOOOOOOOOOOOHOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!
trolling motor about to go on  batteries and charger in  lots of room almost time to fill with rods  is that glove box ever big big big
That is pretty awesome Terry. Congrats!
Very nice Terry, glad you finally have it, and I look forward to your reports from it   Now when will it get slimed???

thanks all  slime no slime in this boat everyone hangs over the side to unhook the fish....lol....ok a little slime maybe '''   man it's hot, might have to do the work on it during the graveyard shift
dayum that is one sexy looking boat Terry !
When do I get to drive it???????  Nice rig buddy.
Very nice! I'll kept an eye out for you on Simcoe.
nice boat man! A bit of an upgrade from the portaboat eh?  Have fun with it! Thanks again for your help with the boat launch location!
Congrats Terry,looks sweet!!!!
Great boat Terry congrats to you can't wait to see it get slimed
thanks guys
She's a beauty! Congrats and enjoy!
Congrats Terry, what an awesome ride!!!

Got the same boat last year and just love it. It has done everything I wanted it to do with flying colours! My only issue is getting a good downrigger setup but I'm working on that. It will give you years of pleasure. Enjoy !!!
sweet ride. Love the rod storage ideas they have in the new editions.   Me thinks you'll be slimed in no time
That is one SWEET ride!!!  Congrats!
Sweet rig! Gotta get me one like that!
Finally!! Now, go slime it!  Great rig!  S.

Awesome boat! IMO you can't beat a Lund. I sold my 1625 Rebel and picked up my 1750 Tyee with 115hp and the 9.9 pro kicker a month ago,pretty much same boat as yours.I put two cannon mag 10s on it. Still haven't fully broken her in yet but I absolutely love this boat when I got it I was like a 6 year old on Christmas day. Enjoy! See you out there
thanks  can't wait to get out
X2. Enjoy
Terry... is there a cover for the battery area.?? Your reels and line won't appreciate those vented batteries!
